# Post‑Release Cycle

## Overview
The Post‑Release Cycle defines the structured actions taken after the book goes live.  
Its purpose is to maintain visibility, engage readers, and extend the lifespan of the launch beyond the initial release window.

---

## Phase 1 — Immediate Post‑Launch (Days 1–7)
- Share launch announcement across all platforms  
- Repost early reader impressions  
- Highlight key themes from the book  
- Reinforce availability on all Kindle platforms  
- Respond to early engagement and messages  

---

## Phase 2 — Engagement Expansion (Weeks 2–4)
- Share excerpts or short quotes  
- Release behind‑the‑scenes insights  
- Post author reflections  
- Highlight global availability  
- Re‑share promotional materials from the Storefront Pack  
- Encourage community discussion  

---

## Phase 3 — Sustained Visibility (Month 2–3)
- Weekly highlight posts  
- Thematic discussions based on book content  
- Occasional reposts of launch materials  
- Reader Q&A moments  
- Community appreciation posts  

---

## Phase 4 — Long‑Tail Presence (Month 4+)
- Monthly spotlight posts  
- Seasonal or event‑based tie‑ins  
- Re‑engagement prompts for new readers  
- Integration into future projects or announcements  

---

## Purpose
This cycle ensures:
- Continued visibility  
- Ongoing reader engagement  
- Long‑term relevance  
- Smooth transition into future releases  

---

## Status
The Post‑Release Cycle is complete, structured, and ready for activation once the book is live.
